  "body": "since the ENS name is not being set in Profile when it is set in settings, it causes a lot of issues when chatting / transacting with mobile, please assist with fixing the issue\r\n\r\n**Steps:**\r\n\r\n1. create account\r\n2. buy ENS name in ENS names dapp \r\n3. set the ens name as primary\r\n4. check the profile\r\n\r\nAs a result, ens name is not replacing 3-words-name even it is being set as primary name\r\n\r\n`DBG 2021-06-03 12:55:01+03:00 Verifying mailserver connection state...   topics=\"mailserver model\" tid=2931892 file=model.nim:186\r\nqrc:/app/AppLayouts/Chat/ChatColumn/MessageComponents/UserImage.qml:9:5: Unable to assign [undefined] to QString\r\nqrc:/app/AppLayouts/Chat/ChatColumn/MessageComponents/UsernameLabel.qml:43:9: Unable to assign [undefined] to QString\r\nqrc:/app/AppLayouts/Chat/ChatColumn/MessageComponents/UsernameLabel.qml:42: ReferenceError: userName is not defined\r\nqrc:/app/AppLayouts/Chat/ChatColumn/MessageComponents/ChatTime.qml:10: ReferenceError: isImage is not defined`\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1012\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-06-03 at 12 17 28\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/82375995/120624853-c6bfc980-c469-11eb-89ae-b79ce4099d62.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1012\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-06-03 at 12 17 24\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/82375995/120624874-caebe700-c469-11eb-9a56-b48055777cd6.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe idea is coming from mobile app: when having ENS name bought and set up in settings -> share profile URL looks like `https://join.status.im/u/tanyatest10.stateofus.eth`\r\n\r\nCurrently on desktop even having ENS name bought and set in profile, share your profile link looks as follows: `https://join.status.im/u/0x0461904235fb5762daf2970bd61b070784f3705fc51d5c96ea798d81a6552599c4f6c88ba9e83686080710b419dbdcca7a5c5ff9e8de7dd58f38a1c8be4c9a5a1d`\r\n\r\nWould be great to implement the feature the way is is present on mobile, so once i buy ENS name and set some in Chat settings -> Primary Username -> Share Profile link will contain the selected ENS name. \r\n\r\nClicking such link should behave the same as for the link with chat key -> sending to user profile.\r\n\r\n@errorists @simonricoo \r\n",
